I telephoned Ms. Thomas to inform her that her claim had been
adjudicated yesterday, 1/12, and that she was found eligible for UI
benefits.  A debit card will be mailed to her this morning and should
take a week to ten days.  At present 7 weeks of benefits are on the
debit card.

I also discussed with Ms. Thomas what seemed to be happening when she
visited the Fayetteville Local Office.  She would attempt to file her
weekly certifications by computer at the local office and would receive
a message stating that her claim had been revoked.  Each time she would
question it, staff seemed to treat her "strangely" and twice asked to
see her Social Security card.  I asked her if she had ever had any
problems with identity theft, as this sounded like a message our
computer system would generate if another claim had been filed with the
same SSN.  I cannot imagine why the local office staff did not explain
the problem to her, especially when she could prove she was the true
owner of that SSN.  Ms. Thomas is satisfied with our apology, thrilled
to be receiving her benefits and glad to know what was happening.  I
have forwarded the problem in the Fayetteville local office to the
proper channels for discussion and customer service training as necessary.

