I telephoned Mr. Lewis and explained to him that the laws governing UI
benefits precluded the Adjudicator and the Appeals Referee from ruling
for his being eligible because he quit his job to relocate with his
spouse.  He felt that the fact of his mother-in-law's illness should
have been taken into consideration, but I explained that the laws and
regulations do not take reasons for relocating into account.  I
explained to Mr. Lewis that only legislators can change the law
governing UI benefits and that we must apply it to claims as the law
currently exists.  Mr. Lewis plans to contact the legislator
representing the NC County of his last residence to lobby for a change
of law.

I further suggested that Mr. Lewis appeal the determination of the
Appeals Referee when he receives it in the mail in case there was some
technicality in the hearing that the Commission attorney reviewing the
case could use to reverse the original decision.  He seemed to
appreciate the contact from ESC.

